dcterms:creator: Ali Najaﬁ
Ramin Golestanian
dcterms:description: The dataset consists of a model for a simple swimmer at low Reynolds number, specifically a three-sphere swimmer, which is used to study hydrodynamics and solute transport.
dcterms:title: Najaﬁ-Golestanian three-sphere swimmer model

dcterms:creator: Stevens Paz
Gustavo C Buscaglia
dcterms:description: This dataset involves the simulation of squirmers using volumetric solvers, which are relevant for understanding the dynamics of self-propelled particles.
dcterms:title: Squirmers

dcterms:creator: Roberto Federico Ausas
Cristian Guillermo Gebhardt
Gustavo Carlos Buscaglia
dcterms:description: This dataset presents a finite element method for simulating soft active non-shearable rods immersed in generalized Newtonian fluids, which is applicable to flexible swimmers.
dcterms:title: Flexible swimmers

dcterms:creator: Roland Clift
John R Grace
Martin E Weber
dcterms:description: Clift's formula provides a theoretical framework for understanding the behavior of towed spheres in fluid dynamics, particularly in relation to nutrient flux.
dcterms:title: Clift's formula for towed sphere

dcterms:creator: L Karp-Boss
E Boss
PA Jumars
dcterms:description: The Karp-Boss nutrient flux model describes nutrient fluxes to planktonic osmotrophs in the presence of fluid motion, providing insights into nutrient dynamics in aquatic environments.
dcterms:title: Karp-Boss nutrient flux model

dcterms:creator: Christopher JCH Watkins
Peter Dayan
dcterms:description: The Q-learning algorithm is a reinforcement learning method that can be applied to various tasks, including chemotaxis in the context of swimmer models.
dcterms:title: Q-learning algorithm for chemotaxis

Maximilian H¨ubl
Gerhard Kahl
Andreas Z¨ottl
dcterms:description: This dataset involves a genetic learning algorithm applied to a three-sphere swimmer, demonstrating its ability to learn chemotaxis in various environments.
dcterms:title: Genetic learning algorithm for three-sphere swimmer
